Reclaimer Shawn = Programming, Form Designing, Address Finding Dark Byte = Bypassing Memory Protection Zanzer = RNG & Programming StarsMmd = For Disabling the Colosseum Shiny Pokemon Glitch & Address Finding Nintendo = For Creating the Pokemon Franchise Dolphin = For Creating the Emulator this game was played on ]]
AboutText=[[ All this program does is use the OS Time and puts that through a formula to make a seed, then based on that generates values within the range of applyable things in the game. In order to use this program, open up Pokemon XD: Gale of Darkness in Dolphin emulator and wait until you see "Press Any Button To Conitnue" Afterwards, press hook game one time(or it might not work properly) To sync the health, press the one button on the keyboard to sync the health of the top slot pokemon. Press 2 to sync the bottom pokemon's health. If you use this several times during a battle, you will completely restore their health. Also, press 1 and 2 when a battle is supposed to end and you can continue it! The Difficulty Scaler has several modes. Pitiful mode spawns Level 1 Pokemon that are a 1 hit knock-out. Normal Mode spawns pokemon within a Level 50 stat range. Intermediate Mode generates pokemon within a Level 75 stat range. Hard Mode generates Pokemon at a Level 100 range. Finally, Impossible mode makes pokemon have an HP stat of 32767 and all other stats are 65535 (Making them impossible to kill save for one or two methods...) Do not use the difficulty scaler in the middle of a battle; scale it after the battle ends if you don't like the mode you're on at the time. If you choose to not check randomize shadow pokemon, shadow pokemon species and stats will still be modified, but shadow pokemon will always appear in their typical places. Finally, do not click on any of the buttons before the game is hooked. You will get a stack overflow and will have to taskill the exe. Then, you'd have to reopen both the program and a new process of Dolphin(Closing the old one out) ]]
